# Fluff Date: 2026-02-16 11:04:06
overview:<p>The Kodiak is a hundred-ton assault BattleMech designed by Clan Ghost Bear as a second-line counterpart to the Executioner. Introduced in 3001, the Kodiak serves as the totem 'Mech of the Ghost Bear Clan, embodying their philosophy of combining heavy defense with surprising speed and devastating firepower. Originally developed alongside the Executioner, the two designs were initially conceived as a single project to create an Omni-Totem 'Mech, but early prototypes proved the Kodiak chassis was incompatible with MASC, forcing the Ghost Bears to split development into separate programs. The result was a purpose-built assault platform that prioritized raw combat power over flexibility, becoming one of the most feared second-line designs in the Clan toumans. Produced primarily at Bergan Industries on Alshain with additional production on Bearclaw, the Kodiak has seen widespread service throughout the Ghost Bear Dominion and later the Rasalhague Dominion, with smaller numbers finding their way into several other Clan toumans.</p>

capabilities:<p>The Kodiak's defining feature is its mammoth 400-rated extra-light engine, which propels the hundred-ton assault 'Mech to speeds of sixty-four kilometers per hour—exceptional mobility for a design of its mass. This speed allows Ghost Bear MechWarriors to close rapidly with their targets, where the Kodiak's devastating close-range arsenal can be brought to bear. The primary armament centers on a Series II Ultra-class autocannon/20 occupying the entire right torso, capable of delivering punishing salvos that can cripple most opponents in a single engagement. Twin Type XII Streak SRM-6 launchers complement the autocannon, ensuring every missile fired finds its mark.</p><p>Eight Series 2a extended-range medium lasers, arrayed in distinctive claw-like mounts on each arm, provide substantial firepower at medium ranges and serve as the primary weapons once ammunition is expended. A single Series 7k extended-range large laser mounted beneath the engine provides the Kodiak's only true long-range capability, allowing pilots to soften targets during their approach. Seventeen and a half tons of Compound 12A2 armor provide impressive protection, though the design's greatest weakness is its prodigious heat generation—firing all weapons simultaneously overwhelms the twenty double heat sinks, forcing MechWarriors to exercise careful fire discipline. While the 'Mech appears to mount claws on each hand, these are purely aesthetic, a nod toward the Totem 'Mech aesthetic rather than functional melee weapons.</p>

deployment:<p>First appearing during the Dominion-Combine War on Richmond in 3062, this variant addresses two of the base Kodiak's most notable shortcomings. The addition of jump jets provides the ability to leap up to one hundred and twenty meters, dramatically increasing tactical mobility and allowing the assault 'Mech to navigate difficult terrain that would otherwise channel its approach. To accommodate the jump jets while managing the design's chronic overheating, four medium lasers and one Streak SRM-6 launcher were removed, significantly reducing heat buildup while maintaining the devastating core combination of the Ultra AC/20 and extended-range large laser.</p>

history:<p>The Kodiak traces its origins to an ambitious Ghost Bear project begun during the Golden Century to create an assault-weight Totem 'Mech incorporating OmniMech technology. After acquiring design schematics for the Executioner through a Trial with Clan Burrock, Ghost Bear scientists attempted to splice the two programs together into a single fast assault OmniMech that would also serve as the Clan's totem. Late in the redesign process, however, prototypes revealed the Kodiak chassis was fundamentally incompatible with MASC, and the project was split in 3001 into two separate designs: the Executioner OmniMech and the Kodiak, a purpose-built second-line assault BattleMech. Though it never received the flexibility of an OmniMech, the Kodiak's raw combination of speed, armor, and devastating close-range firepower made it one of the most feared assault platforms in any Clan touman.</p><p>For decades following its introduction, the Kodiak remained exclusive to Clan Ghost Bear, produced at Bergan Industries on Alshain and a secondary facility designated Ghost Bear Facility Beta-1 on Bearclaw. The design was closely guarded as befitting a Totem 'Mech, but the realities of inter-Clan politics gradually saw small numbers enter other toumans. Clan Snow Raven obtained the largest share outside the Ghost Bears, reportedly as partial payment for their critical assistance during the Ghost Bear relocation to the Inner Sphere. Clans Cloud Cobra and Goliath Scorpion also acquired limited numbers through various exchanges, while among the Crusader Clans, only Clan Ice Hellion managed to field a handful of these prestigious machines.</p><p>The Kodiak first drew significant Inner Sphere attention during the Clan Invasion, where Ghost Bear assault Stars spearheaded drives across multiple worlds with devastating effect. The design's fearsome reputation grew as Inner Sphere forces learned to respect its combination of assault-class firepower and heavy-medium speed. During Operation Bulldog, the discovery of at least two Kodiaks within a Smoke Jaguar unit on Asgard demonstrated the design's proliferation well beyond its original touman, raising questions about how the Jaguars had obtained them.</p><p>The Dominion-Combine War of 3062 proved a watershed moment for the Kodiak program. The newly developed Kodiak 2 received its baptism of fire on Richmond, where its enhanced mobility from jump jets proved decisive in the close urban fighting that characterized that campaign. Clan Hell's Horses subsequently obtained at least a Trinary of Kodiaks from the Ghost Bears through Trials of Possession, further expanding the design's operational footprint. Meanwhile, Clan Snow Raven's innate aerospace bias led their scientists to develop the radical Kodiak 3 anti-aircraft variant in the mid-3060s, leveraging dual LB 20-X autocannons and an advanced targeting computer to create a ground-based platform specifically tailored to counter aerospace threats. This variant entered refit production at facilities on Dante, initially aboard the orbital Eden Rose Potemkin-class facility before transitioning to the surface-based Snow Raven Industrial Complex Alpha around 3076.</p><p>The transition from the Ghost Bear Dominion to the Rasalhague Dominion brought both upheaval and renewal to Kodiak production. The Alshain facility—operating under various names across the centuries from Bergan Industries to Alshain Weapons—remained the primary production center, while the Bearclaw facility passed through Snow Raven and Star Lion control before its later fate became uncertain. Gorton, Kingsley, and Thorpe Enterprises on Satalice began producing the Kodiak 6 variant in 3131, expanding the manufacturing base and introducing GK&T's own refinements to the venerable design. A recovered Kodiak on Dieron was refitted with mixed Inner Sphere and Clan technology, serving as a capable command platform for Draconis Combine forces—a testament to how far the once-exclusive Totem 'Mech had spread across the Inner Sphere.</p><p>The Kodiak 4 variant, with its hybrid missile and ballistic loadout, proved so successful that it directly inspired the development of the Kodiak II command 'Mech in 3095, ensuring the Kodiak lineage would continue shaping Dominion military doctrine well into the thirty-second century. More than a century and a half after its introduction, the Kodiak remains a symbol of Ghost Bear martial tradition and a reminder that even without OmniMech flexibility, a well-designed BattleMech can endure across eras of warfare.</p>

